<hr />

<p>To use your external captive portal solution with CT WiFi just follow these simple steps.</p>

<div class="mdl-typography--text-center">
<img src="/images/community/tutorials/external-captive-portal/externalsplash.gif" />
</div>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Head into your <strong>Location</strong> on your dashboard.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Select <strong>SSIDs</strong> on the left sidebar, and click <strong>View</strong> on the SSID you want to have an external captive portal on.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Scroll down to the <strong>Captive Portal</strong> section, and the <strong>Advanced Settings</strong> header under that.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Unselect <strong>Use CT WiFi Splash</strong> &amp; <strong>Use CT WiFi Radius</strong> and you will see new fields appear.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Enter the required information into the fields and then save your changes.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<hr />

<p><em>CT WiFi is a cloud based WiFi management platform for businesses. The firmware gives consumer-grade WiFi access points enterprise-like capabilities.Or you can utlise the captive portal solution with your existing infrastructure. Create a free account and check it here <a href="https://ct-networks.io">ct-networks.io</a></em></p>

